U.S. Stocks Extend Drop as Japan Earthquake Shakes Tokyo

-- B y   M i c h a e l   P .   R e g a n
-- 
2011-04-07T14:42:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-07/u-s-stocks-drop-after-second-japan-quake-in-less-than-month-shakes-tokyo.html
U.S. stocks extended losses after a
magnitude 7.4 earthquake shook  Japan , less than a month after
the nation’s worst temblor on record.  The Standard & Poor’s 500 Index slid 0.6 percent to 1,327.6
at 10:41 a.m. in  New York . The  Dow Jones Industrial Average  lost
85.98 points, or 0.7 percent, to 12,340.77  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
